.TH SNORTSENTRY 8 "December 1, 2025" "snortsentry v8.1.6" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
snortsentry \- Snort alert processor and dynamic PF blocker for OpenBSD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B snortsentry
.RB [ \-a
.I file
.RB ] [ \-f
.I file
.RB ] [ \-l
.I file
.RB ] [ \-p
.I file
.RB ] [ \-s
.I file
.RB ] [ \-t
.I table
.RB ] [ \-Dhnv ] [ \-\-log
.I file
.RB ] [ \-\-status ] [ \-\-version ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B snortsentry
is a highly resilient, Perl-based daemon that monitors Snort IDS alert logs
and dynamically blocks offending source IP addresses using OpenBSD's Packet
Filter (PF).

It robustly parses Snort alerts, manages block duration escalation for repeat
offenders, and uses **atomic file operations with checksums** for reliable
state persistence across reboots. The program supports both **IPv4 and IPv6**
addresses.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f \fIfile\fP
Specify configuration file (default: /etc/snort/snortsentry.conf).
.TP
.B \-a \fIfile\fP
Specify Snort alert file (default: /var/log/snort/alert).
.TP
.B \-p \fIfile\fP
Specify PID file (default: /var/run/snortsentry.pid).
.TP
.B \-l \fIfile\fP
Specify lock file (default: /var/run/snortsentry.lock).
.TP
.B \-s \fIfile\fP
Specify state file (default: /var/db/snortsentry.state).
.TP
.B \-\-log \fIfile\fP
Specify log file (optional).
.TP
.B \-t \fItable\fP
Specify PF table name (default: snort_block).
.TP
.B \-v
Enable verbose (debug) logging.
.TP
.B \-D
Run in foreground (don't daemonize).
.TP
.B \-n
Dry run mode (parses alerts but does not modify PF).
.TP
.B \-h
Show help message.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-status
Show current running status. (Returns process ID if running).

.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file (default: /etc/snort/snortsentry.conf) supports the following options:

.TP
.B AlertFile \fIpath\fP
Path to Snort alert file.
.TP
.B StateFile \fIpath\fP
Path to state file for persistence.
.TP
.B BlockDuration \fIseconds\fP
Initial block duration (default: 60).
.TP
.B MaxBlockDuration \fIseconds\fP
Maximum block duration (default: 86400).
.TP
.B Priority \fInumber\fP
Minimum alert priority to trigger blocking (1=highest, default: 1).
.TP
.B EnableEscalation \fIyes|no\fP
Enable block duration escalation (default: yes).
.TP
.B EscalationTiers \fIseconds[,seconds...]\fP
Comma-separated list of durations for subsequent blocks.
.TP
.B PfTable \fIname\fP
PF table name (default: snort_block).
.TP
.B UseAnchor \fIyes|no\fP
Toggles between Anchor Mode and Table Only Mode (default: yes).
.TP
.B AutoWhitelistRFC1918 \fIyes|no\fP
Automatically whitelist RFC1918/link-local addresses (default: yes).
.TP
.B Keyword \fI"pattern"\fP
Alert message patterns to match (case-insensitive regex).
.TP
.B Whitelist \fIip1 [ip2...]\fP
IPs or CIDR blocks to whitelist.
.TP
.B CheckInterval \fIseconds\fP
Alert file check interval (default: 1).
.TP
.B UnblockOnExit \fIyes|no\fP
Remove all IPs from PF table on graceful exit (default: no).
.TP
.B LogLevel \fIdebug|info|warn|error\fP
Log level (default: info).

.SH PF SETUP
.B snortsentry
is optimized for stability using PF tables.

.SS Table Only Mode (Recommended)
This mode (\fBUseAnchor no\fP) requires the block rules to be manually defined in
\fIpf.conf\fP. This prevents conflicts with other dynamically updated tables.

.RS
.nf
table <snort_block> persist
block drop quick from <snort_block> to any
block drop quick inet6 from <snort_block> to any
.fi
.RE

.SS Anchor Mode Caveat
If \fBUseAnchor yes\fP (the default) is maintained, you must ensure your \fIpf.conf\fP
loads the anchor (\fBanchor "snort_block" all\fP). This mode may lead to warnings
or conflicts when other non-anchor tables are dynamically refreshed.

.SH SERVICE MANAGEMENT
The service is managed via \fBrcctl(8)\fP using the \fI/etc/rc.d/snortsentry\fP script.

.TP
Start service:
.B rcctl start snortsentry
.TP
Reload configuration (sends SIGHUP):
.B rcctl reload snortsentry
.TP
Check running status:
.B rcctl check snortsentry
.TP
Manual process lookup:
.B pgrep -f snortsentry

.SH NOTES
.TP
.B NetAddr::IP Compatibility
This version of snortsentry is designed for maximum compatibility with older
OpenBSD systems running NetAddr::IP v3.x. Consequently, the optional feature to
rewrite IPv4-mapped IPv6 addresses (::ffff:x.x.x.x) to pure IPv4 is disabled
to ensure stability.

.TP
.B Permissions
The daemon requires root privileges to execute \fBpfctl(8)\fP.

.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Reload configuration from \fB\-f\fP file.
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Graceful shutdown.
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Dump statistics to log.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/local/sbin/snortsentry
Main executable script.
.TP
.B /etc/snort/snortsentry.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.B /var/db/snortsentry.state
Default state file.
.TP
.B /etc/rc.d/snortsentry
rcctl(8) control script.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start in foreground with verbose logging:
.B snortsentry -D -v -f /etc/snort/snortsentry.conf

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pf.conf (5),
.BR pfctl (8),
.BR snort (8),
.BR rcctl (8)
